article.description: — Michael Anumba had 15 points in Winthrop's 83-74 win against South Carolina Upstate on Saturday.
article.headline: Anumba's 15 help Winthrop beat South Carolina Upstate 83-74
article.linkText: Anumba's 15 help Winthrop beat South Carolina Upstate 83-74
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. -- — Michael Anumba had 15 points in Winthrop's 83-74 win against South Carolina Upstate on Saturday. Anumba added five rebounds for the Eagles (17-12, 8-6 Big South Conference). Sin'Cere McMahon scored 13 points, shooting 4 for 13, including 3 for 9 from beyond the arc. Kelton Talford had 12 points and shot 5 of 6 from the field and 2 for 3 from the line. Trae Broadnax led the Spartans (9-19, 4-11) in scoring, finishing with 22 points and six rebounds. Justin Bailey added 15 points for South Carolina Upstate. Jalen Breazeale also had 15 points and eight assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
